Face Mask Detector

📁 Project Structure
face-mask-detection/
│
├── deep_learning.ipynb          # Main training notebook
├── mask_detector_cnn_best.h5   # Saved best model (generated after training)
├── label_map.json              # Index-to-label mapping {0: "with_mask", 1: "without_mask"}
├── deploy.prototxt             # OpenCV DNN SSD face detector config
├── res10_300x300_ssd_iter_140000.caffemodel  # Pre-trained face detector weights
└── README.md

📦 Dataset

Source: Kaggle — Face Mask Dataset by omkargurav
Classes: 2

with_mask — ~3725 images
without_mask — ~3828 images


Folder structure expected:
data/
  with_mask/
    image1.jpg
    image2.jpg
    ...
  without_mask/
    image1.jpg
    ...
pip install tensorflow keras numpy matplotlib scikit-learn opencv-python kagglehub

GPU recommended. Notebook is optimized for Kaggle P100. Mixed precision (float16) is enabled for speed.

🚀 How to Run
Step 1 — Download Dataset
pythonimport kagglehub
path = kagglehub.dataset_download("omkargurav/face-mask-dataset")
Step 2 — Train the Model
Run all cells in deep_learning.ipynb. The notebook will:

Load and augment images via ImageDataGenerator
Build and compile the CNN
Train with EarlyStopping (max 30 epochs)
Save the best model to mask_detector_cnn_best.h5

Step 3 — Run Inference
out = robust_predict("/path/to/your/image.jpg", show=True)
print(out)
# {'status': 'ok', 'method': 'dnn_ssd', 'predictions': [{'box': [...], 'label': 'with_mask', 'confidence': 0.97}]}

🧠 Model Architecture
Input (128 × 128 × 3)
     │
Conv2D(32, 3×3, relu) → BatchNorm → MaxPool → Dropout(0.25)
     │
Conv2D(64, 3×3, relu) → BatchNorm → MaxPool → Dropout(0.25)
     │
Conv2D(128, 3×3, relu) → BatchNorm → MaxPool → Dropout(0.3)
     │
Flatten
     │
Dense(128, relu) → BatchNorm → Dropout(0.4)
     │
Dense(1, sigmoid)   ← Output: 0 = with_mask, 1 = without_mask

Why this architecture?

3 Conv blocks progressively extract features: edges → shapes → high-level patterns
BatchNormalization keeps training stable
Dropout prevents overfitting
Sigmoid output works for binary (2-class) classification

🛑 Callbacks
EarlyStopping
pythonEarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', patience=6, restore_best_weights=True)
Stops training if validation loss doesn't improve for 6 consecutive epochs. Restores the best weights automatically.
ModelCheckpoint
pythonModelCheckpoint('mask_detector_cnn_best.h5', monitor='val_accuracy', save_best_only=True)
Saves model only when validation accuracy hits a new best.

🔍 Inference Pipeline
At prediction time, the notebook uses OpenCV DNN SSD for face detection:
Input Image
     │
DNN SSD Face Detector  ← Finds face bounding boxes
     │
Crop + Pad each face
     │
Resize to 128×128, normalize
     │
CNN predicts → prob > 0.5 → "without_mask"
                prob ≤ 0.5 → "with_mask"
     │
Draw bounding box + label on image
If no face is detected → prediction is skipped. This prevents classifying non-face images (e.g. apples, dogs) incorrectly.

📊 Evaluation
After training, the notebook prints:
Validation Accuracy: XX.XX%

Classification Report:
              precision  recall  f1-score
  with_mask      0.xx    0.xx     0.xx
